These models of antigenically evolving populations are related to general models of rapid adaptation in which populations form a traveling wave moving towards higher fitness (
 Tsimring et al., 1996; 
 Rouzine et al., 2003; 
 Desai and Fisher, 2007; 
 Neher et al., 2014), reviewed in 
 Neher (2013a). Recently, 
 Rouzine and Rozhnova (2018) described an explicit mapping between a SIR model in a one-dimensional antigenic space and traveling wave models in fitness.
